title: Never Seen Star Wars
alt: If anyone calls you on any weird detail, just say it's from the Jedi Prince book series, which contains so much random incongruous stuff that even most Expanded Universe/Legends fans collectively agreed to forget about it decades ago.
transcript:
White Hat: You know the scene on the Death Star where—
Cueball: Nah, I've never seen Star Wars.White Hat: WHAT.White Hat: …How?!
Cueball: Uh, it was easy?
Cueball: It was literally the default option.White Hat: But… How did you—
Cueball: Not doing things is my superpower. I'm not doing an infinite number of things as we speak!White Hat: We have to watch it.
Cueball: Nah, I'm good.White Hat: Hey everyone! This guy's never seen Star Wars!
Cueball: Listen, I gotta go.Ponytail: Wait, there's a new Star Wars?
Cueball: Oh, I've nev—
Cueball: …Yeah! Excited for it! Big fan.Ponytail: What'd you think of the last one?
Cueball: Uh… That Darth Vader, man.
Cueball: Sure does love eating Jedi.Ponytail: Haha, he sure does!
Cueball [thinking]: Phew!
Ponytail [thinking]: Phew!
